go 1.26.1

toolchain go1.26.4

// During the refactor we use a Go Workspace to stitch together
// the legacy single-module root (./) and the new per-app /
// per-package modules under apps/ and packages/.
//
// The `go` directive must be >= the highest `go` directive in
// any member module's go.mod. Keep it bumped if any module's
// requirement rises. `toolchain` pins the actual compiler so
// every dev (and CI) uses the same version regardless of what
// they have locally; bump it deliberately and in its own commit.
//
// As each new module lands (apps/api, apps/worker, packages/sqlc,
// packages/domain, packages/riotapi), append it here via:
//   go work use ./apps/api
// and bump this file in the same commit so CI stays green.

use (
	.
)
